[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+     37[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+     38[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mThe measure registry is the source of truth for what counts as a gap, and it has to be curated.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m This example ships with a small synthetic registry of 5 measures across HEDIS and patient-specific patterns. Production needs structured change management with clinical informatics review, parallel evaluation against the prior measure version on a sample, and ongoing reconciliation against your HEDIS vendor's official numbers. Without that, the recommender's gap counts will diverge from the plan's reported HEDIS performance and credibility burns.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+     39[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mThe closure tracker is the part most teams skip and the part that makes or breaks operator trust.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m This example wires the multi-source reconciliation with canonical-source rules per measure. The chase team should never call a patient about a colonoscopy they had last week; the suppression of in-flight outreach on closure-event arrival is what makes that work.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+     40[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mThe clinical urgency model is the second-hardest part.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m Production-grade urgency estimation requires longitudinal outcome data with confounding adjustment (the patients who close their gaps differ from the patients who don't). The training script is out of scope for this companion; the main recipe's "Why This Isn't Production-Ready" section walks through the gap. The example uses a rule-based proxy.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+     41[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mBedrock model IDs change over time.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m Some regions require cross-region inference profile IDs (prefixed [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mus.[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m or [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140meu.[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m). The IDs below are reasonable defaults; verify in the Bedrock console for your region before running.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+     42[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mAll patients, measures, gaps, schedules, and engagement events in the example are synthetic.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m Do not treat any specific patient_id, measure_id, evidence event, or closure event as real. A production system ingests from real claims, EHR, lab, pharmacy, and immunization-registry feeds under BAA.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+     43[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mThe example collapses Step Functions, Glue, Athena, and SageMaker Batch Transform into a single Python file for readability.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m In production these are separate workflow stages with their own error handling, IAM, and DLQs. Comments call out where the boundaries should fall.[K
