[38;5;141m> [0m{"verdict": "pass", "rationale": "The Python companion implements all six steps of the recipe end-to-end (measure evaluation with state machine, urgency/engagement enrichment, visit-context ranking with LLM briefings, multi-pathway async orchestration, multi-source closure tracking, clinician override handling) and ties them together in run_daily_batch with a synthetic demo. boto3 usage is correct across services: DynamoDB resource with Table.put_item/update_item/get_item/scan and proper UpdateExpression/ExpressionAttributeValues/ExpressionAttributeNames (including the Decimal conversion pattern), bedrock-runtime.invoke_model with anthropic_version body, kinesis.put_record with StreamName/PartitionKey/Data, cloudwatch.put_metric_data with Namespace/MetricData/Dimensions, sagemaker.describe_transform_job, athena.get_query_execution, and adaptive retry config. Error handling is thorough: try/except around every external call, structured logging, templated fallbacks for LLM/validator failures, and comments explaining why metrics publishing is best-effort vs. a correctness boundary. The remaining minimal helpers (e.g., [3mcross[23mrecipe_suppresses, [3msuppress[23minflight_outreach, [3mupdate[23mtraining_label) are clearly scoped as integration boundaries to external systems with explicit 'Production:' guidance rather than core recipe logic, and the rule-based urgency/engagement scorers contain real logic rather than empty stubs. Demo mocks are applied only at the [1mmain[22m runner level so the offline demo is reproducible without altering production paths."}[0m[1G[0m[0m[?25h